  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nIf the `quarkus.http.root-path` is changed, this is not taken into account when specifying `quarkus.http.auth.permission.authenticated.paths`.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n[reproducer.zip](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/files/8405187/reproducer.zip)\r\n\r\n1. http://localhost:8080/hello => User will be asked to sign in\r\n2. Uncomment `quarkus.http.root-path=/example/` in `application.properties`\r\n3. http://localhost:8080/example/hello => No authentication anymore\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nJava 11\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.7.5\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nMaven\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
